Labour Court has reinstated Wilson Sossion as KNUT Secretary-General days after he was ousted by the union's Â National Executive Council. Employment and labour relations Judge Hellen Wasilwa suspended Knut's NEC decision to kick out Sossion. The judge has further said only Knut's registered officials prior to August 29 will operate the union's bank accounts held at KCB. Sossion has also been allowed to access office his office and bank accounts waiting for the determination of his case. More to follow...